    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 19th with a high-ceiling offensive setup, headlined by **Junior Caminero** (74.54) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (74.43). **Junior Caminero** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Keller, and the added tailwind helps push his score into the elite tier. Meanwhile, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** remains a top priority despite the defensive threat of an elite catcher, as his dynamic platoon advantage against Myers and his elite sprint speed\u2014our most precious commodity\u2014make him an absolute must-start. **Trea Turner** (70.45) and **Carson Benge** (67.24) also provide strong production today, with the latter capitalizing on a prime matchup against Assad\u2019s shaky 4.83 xERA.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical adjustments today. **Chase Meidroth** (62.45) earned his spot as a top play thanks to a massive 14% boost from Springs\u2019 matchup profile and an advantageous leadoff slot, while **Kyle Schwarber** (66.90) and **Yordan Alvarez** (64.44) provide reliable, high-floor power despite facing left-handed starters. The most difficult benching decision was **Josh Smith**, who fell just short of our 40.0 \"Below Floor\" cutoff with a score of 39.29. While he offers some platoon value against Woo, the poor SP skill adjustment and a lower-order lineup spot ultimately kept him on the bench to preserve our game caps. Be advised that **Victor Scott II** (46.01) is starting despite a suppressed score; we are prioritizing his stolen base potential over pure offensive efficiency, though his bottom-of-the-order placement remains a drag on his overall output. No significant weather hazards are flagged, but we will monitor the lineup status for **Caleb Durbin**, whose ability to exploit Valdez\u2019s slow delivery keeps him in the UTIL slot despite the tough lefty matchup.",
